# Installation/Re-installation from Inventory


**Important Notes**

- In case of Re-installation request from Customer, make sure that Customer Agreed with DATA LOSS

Follow the procedure to reinstall server using Inventory

- Login to inventory
- Search server with its SN from inventory

- Netboot server by clicking on Netboot
- In the next window select the OS template from the drop down list and then click on install

- In case RAID array is already created and you want to use same RAID array, then you can use "RAID already setup"
- If customer have specific requirement like RAID5, or RAID1 etc, then you can select appropriate option in installation.
- In case you are not sure then use RAID1 for 2x drives RAID, and RAID10 for 4x drives.

- You can keep pinging server ip, and if it go down then it means server is rebooted and will be installing OS

- After you get login in gmail, it may take 30-60 minute depending on operating system to run updates and after that server will be accessible for you. Linux updates are faster then Windows, therefore some times windows server take 1-2 hours to be able to accessible through remote desktop after password arrive in gmail.
- By default, Windows allowing full hard drive to C partition. Mostly customers do not care about it. However in case customer ask for specific requirement of C Partition, then you can resize disk by login to Windows >> Disk Management
- When Installing RAID server, you do not need to install 3ware/mega raid monitoring. Now system automatically install monitoring with OS installation, and RAID status will be displayed on client portal in case of any error.
